To make a product safety inquiry with Oxford University Press, you can use the contact information provided on the Oxford Learner's Dictionaries website:

1. **Email**: Send your inquiry to **eltdict.help@oup.com**. Include details about the product safety concern, any relevant URLs or screenshots, and your contact information.
2. **Phone**: Call **+44 (0)1865 521498** during business hours (08:00 – 17:00 GMT, Monday‑Friday) to speak directly with the support team.

These contact details are listed on the **Legal Notice** page of the site (https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/us/legal-notice) under the "Queries" section, which handles concerns about material on the website, including product safety issues.

You can also navigate to the Legal Notice page from the homepage by scrolling to the footer and clicking the "Legal Notice" link, then locating the "Queries" section for the contact information.


